.Dd April 4, 2026
.Dt RETROWAVE 1
.Os
.Sh NAME
.Nm retrowave
.Nd terminal music player with ASCII album art, playlists, and LRC lyrics
.Sh SYNOPSIS
.Nm
.Op Ar file_or_directory ...
.Sh DESCRIPTION
.Nm
is a local terminal music player for browsing directories of music, decoding tracks with FFmpeg, rendering album art as ASCII, and showing synchronized lyrics from nearby
.Pa .lrc
files.
If no input paths are provided,
.Nm
scans the current working directory recursively for supported audio files.
.Sh FEATURES
.Bl -bullet -compact
.It
Playlist navigation in an
.Xr ncurses 3
interface
.It
Playback through macOS AudioToolbox
.It
ASCII album card rendered from embedded cover art or nearby image files
.It
Animated visualizer with auto gain
.It
Lyrics mode backed by local
.Pa .lrc
files
.El
.Sh HOTKEYS
.Bl -tag -width Ds
.It Up / Down
Move playlist selection
.It Enter
Play selected track
.It Space
Pause or resume playback
.It n
Play next track
.It p
Play previous track
.It + / -
Adjust volume
.It t
Toggle between visualizer and lyrics panel
.It w
Show warranty notice
.It c
Show redistribution notice
.It q
Quit
.El
.Sh LYRICS
Lyrics are loaded from a file with the same stem as the current track, for example:
.Pp
.Dl song.mp3
.Dl song.lrc
.Pp
Timed LRC lines are highlighted and auto-scrolled during playback.
If no matching
.Pa .lrc
file is found, the lyrics panel reports that lyrics are unavailable.
.Sh ALBUM ART
Album art is loaded from embedded attached pictures when available.
If embedded art is missing,
.Nm
looks for nearby files named:
.Pp
.Dl cover.jpg
.Dl cover.png
.Dl folder.jpg
.Dl front.jpg
.Dl album.jpg
.Sh SUPPORTED FORMATS
.Nm
relies on FFmpeg for decoding and supports common formats including:
.Pp
.Dl mp3, flac, wav, m4a, ogg, opus, aac, aiff, alac, wma
.Sh EXAMPLES
.Bl -tag -width Ds
.It
Play everything under the current directory:
.Pp
.Dl retrowave
.It
Play a specific music folder:
.Pp
.Dl retrowave ~/Music
.It
Open this manual from the project root:
.Pp
.Dl MANPATH="$PWD/man" man retrowave
.El
.Sh FILES
.Bl -tag -width Ds
.It Pa man/man1/retrowave.1
Project manual page
.It Pa *.lrc
Optional local lyrics files placed next to tracks
.El
.Sh EXIT STATUS
.Ex -std
.Sh AUTHORS
.Nm
was built as a local C++ terminal player project.
